        <p data-uuid="efa60484012941c0b3890ea57563ee91">Some New England writers and philosophers found spiritual wisdom in <b><dfn title="transcendentalism">transcendentalism</dfn></b>, the
            belief that people could transcend, or rise above, material things in life.
            Transcendentalists also believed that people should depend on themselves and
            their own insights, rather than on outside authorities. Important
            transcendentalists included <b><dfn title="Emerson, Ralph Waldo">Ralph
            Waldo Emerson</dfn></b>, <b><dfn title="Fuller, Margaret">Margaret
            Fuller</dfn></b>, and <b><dfn title="Thoreau, Henry David">Henry
            David Thoreau</dfn></b>.<br />
        </p>
